  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "To deposit cash at an ATM, typically follow these steps:\n\n1. Insert your bank card into the ATM\n\n2. Enter your PIN\n\n3. Select \"Deposit\" or \"Make a Deposit\" from the menu options\n\n4. Choose the account you want to deposit into (checking or savings)\n\n5. Select \"Cash Deposit\"\n\n6. Take the provided deposit envelope (if required)\n\n7. Insert cash into the envelope and seal it (if using an envelope)\n\n8. Place the envelope/cash directly into the ATM's deposit slot\n\n9. Confirm the deposit amount on the screen\n\n10. Take your receipt and card\n\nNote: Some modern ATMs allow you to deposit cash directly without an envelope. The process can vary slightly depending on your bank and specific ATM, so follow the on-screen instructions carefully.",
